    <p class="sl">How Our Pricing Works</p>
    <h2>Grease buildup is the #1 range hood problem in LA &mdash; and it&rsquo;s often free to diagnose</h2>
    <div class="body-text">
      <p>The most common range hood issues in Los Angeles &mdash; weak suction, loud fan noise, and fan that won&rsquo;t turn off &mdash; are frequently caused by grease buildup rather than component failure. A grease-clogged fan blade causes vibration and imbalance that sounds like a failing motor. A saturated charcoal filter in a ductless hood makes the unit seem ineffective. Flat-rate pricing charges you for a motor replacement before checking whether cleaning alone solves the problem.</p>
      <p>We diagnose first. The $89 fee covers the full diagnosis including duct condition inspection on ducted hoods. If grease buildup is the root cause, that&rsquo;s part of the repair. If a component has actually failed, you get labor and the OEM part as separate numbers before approving anything.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="safety-block">
      <div class="safety-label">&#128293; Fire hazard &mdash; grease buildup in range hood ducts</div>
      <p>Range hood ducts clogged with grease are a kitchen fire hazard. A grease fire that reaches a duct with heavy buildup can spread rapidly. LA Fire Department recommendations call for professional duct cleaning at least annually in households with high-heat cooking. When we diagnose a range hood, we inspect the duct condition and advise on cleaning if needed &mdash; not as an upsell, but as a safety concern.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="type-grid">
      <div class="type-card">
        <h3>&#128268; Ducted range hoods</h3>
        <p>Vents to exterior through a duct. Most effective ventilation. Duct condition matters &mdash; a clogged or restricted duct makes even a working fan ineffective. Duct inspection included in every ducted hood diagnosis.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="type-card">
        <h3>&#9855; Ductless / recirculating</h3>
        <p>Filters and recirculates air. Common in LA condos and apartments without exterior duct access. Charcoal filter replacement is maintenance, not repair &mdash; but clogged filters often cause apparent failure. We check filters before diagnosing the motor.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

