    <p class="sl">FAQ</p>
    <h2>Questions about range hood repair costs in Los Angeles</h2>
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">How much does range hood repair cost in Los Angeles?</div><div class="faq-a">Labor runs $100&ndash;$320 for standard brands. Fan motor replacement is the most common part job and runs $150&ndash;$300. But many hood problems in LA are grease-related and require no parts at all. Parts are quoted separately after diagnosis. Wolf, Miele, and Gaggenau hoods run $240&ndash;$480+ in labor.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Why is my range hood so loud?</div><div class="faq-a">Loud range hood fans in LA are most commonly caused by grease buildup on the fan blades causing imbalance &mdash; not a failing motor. We clean the fan assembly before diagnosing a motor failure. Many loud hood calls in LA resolve with cleaning and no replacement part.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Is a clogged range hood duct dangerous?</div><div class="faq-a">Yes. Grease buildup in a range hood duct is a fire hazard. A grease fire that reaches a clogged duct can spread rapidly. We inspect duct condition on every ducted hood call and advise on cleaning when needed. LA Fire Department recommends annual professional duct cleaning for high-heat cooking households.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Why do you quote labor and parts separately?</div><div class="faq-a">Many LA repair companies use flat-rate BlueBook pricing. A grease cleaning that requires no parts should not cost the same as a motor replacement. We quote separately so the price reflects your actual repair. Grease cleaning is part of the repair when it&rsquo;s the root cause &mdash; not a separate charge.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">Are parts included in the quoted labor price?</div><div class="faq-a">No &mdash; all prices on this page are labor only. Parts quoted separately after diagnosis. Grease cleaning and duct inspection included when relevant &mdash; not a separate charge. OEM parts wherever available.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item"><div class="faq-q">What is the $89 diagnostic fee?</div><div class="faq-a">We charge $89 to come out and diagnose the problem, including duct condition inspection on ducted hoods. That fee applies to the repair total when you approve the work. If you decide not to repair, you pay $89 and we leave.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

